B0123/21 NOTAMR B0121/21 Q) EDXX/QAFXX/IV/NBO/E /000/999/5123N01019E262 A) EDWW EDGG EDMM PART 1 OF 8 B) 2102011336 C) 2104302359 E) COVID-19: CARRIERS/CREWS/PASSENGERS REQUIREMENTS 1. REQUIREMENTS NOTE 1: CARRIERS MUST PROVIDE INFORMATION OF THE GERMAN FEDERAL MINISTRY OF HEALTH TO ALL PAX.
NOTE 2: PLEASE ADVISE PAX TO CHECK TRAVEL RESTRICTIONS, TESTING AND QUARANTINE OBLIGATIONS PRIOR TO DEPARTURE.
NOTE 3: PAX WHO INTEND TO ENTER GERMANY AND WHO HAVE STAYED IN AN INTERNATIONAL RISK AREA (INCLUDING HIGH-INCIDENCE AREA OR AN AREA OF VIRUS VARIANT OF CONCERN) WITHIN THE LAST 10 DAYS PRIOR TO ENTRY ARE SUBJECT TO MANDATORY ENTRY REGISTRATION AND SARS-COV-2 TESTING.
NOTE 4: DESIGNATION OF INTERNATIONAL RISK AREAS, HIGH-INCIDENCE AREAS OR AREAS OF VIRUS VARIANT OF CONCERN: CARRIERS ARE STRONGLY ADVISED TO REGULARLY REVIEW THE DESIGNATION LIST AT WWW.RKI.DE/COVID-19-RISIKOGEBIETE. DESIGNATIONS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE AT SHORT NOTICE. END PART 1 OF 8 B0123/21 NOTAMR B0121/21 Q) EDXX/QAFXX/IV/NBO/E /000/999/5123N01019E262 A) EDWW EDGG EDMM PART 2 OF 8 B) 2102011336 C) 2104302359 E) NOTE 5: PAX WHO INTEND TO ENTER GERMANY AND WHO HAVE STAYED IN AN INTERNATIONAL RISK AREA (INCLUDING HIGH-INCIDENCE AREA OR AN AREA OF VIRUS VARIANT OF CONCERN) WITHIN THE LAST 10 DAYS PRIOR TO ENTRY MUST REGISTER ELECTRONICALLY. USE OF ONLINE PROCEDURE IS STRONGLY ADVISED. PAPER-BASED REGISTRATION IS ONLY ACCEPTED AS A REPLACEMENT IF ELECTRONIC REGISTRATION IS OUT OF ORDER OR PAX DO NOT HAVE ACCESS TO ELECTRONIC REGISTRATION. OFFICIAL SUBSTITUTE REGISTRATION FORM MUST BE USED.
NOTE 6: PROOF OF SUCCESSFUL ENTRY REGISTRATION OR SUBSTITUTE REGISTRATION FORM MUST BE KEPT BY PAX AT ALL TIMES AND PRESENTED ON REQUEST TO THE CARRIER OR THE COMPETENT AUTHORITY.
NOTE 7: PAX RECEIPT OF SUCCESSFUL ENTRY REGISTRATION OR SUBSTITUTE REGISTRATION FORM MUST BE CHECKED BY CARRIERS AGAINST ID CARD OR EQUIVALENT PRIOR BOARDING.
NOTE 8: CARRIERS MUST ONLY TRANSPORT PAX WHO HAVE PRESENTED PROOF OF SUCCESSFUL REGISTRATION OR SUBSTITUTE REGISTRATION FORM. END PART 2 OF 8 B0123/21 NOTAMR B0121/21 Q) EDXX/QAFXX/IV/NBO/E /000/999/5123N01019E262 A) EDWW EDGG EDMM PART 3 OF 8 B) 2102011336 C) 2104302359 E) NOTE 9: ON FLIGHTS FROM SCHENGEN COUNTRIES TO GERMANY SUBSTITUTE REGISTRATION FORM MUST BE COLLECTED BY THE AIRCRAFT CREW AND HANDED OVER TO THE COMPETENT AUTHORITY AT THE DESTINATION AIRPORT IN GERMANY. ON FLIGHTS FROM NON-SCHENGEN COUNTRIES TO GERMANY SUBSTITUTE REGISTRATION MUST BE KEPT BY PAX AND HANDED OVER TO THE FEDERAL POLICE / COMPETENT AUTHORITY AT THE DESTINATION AIRPORT IN GERMANY DURING BORDER CONTROL CHECKS.
NOTE 10: FLIGHTS FROM NON-SCHENGEN COUNTRIES TO GERMANY: REGISTRATION RECEIPT AND SUBSTITUTE REGISTRATION IS SUBJECT TO ADDITIONAL CHECKS BY THE FEDERAL POLICE / COMPETENT AUTHORITY AT DESTINATION AIRPORT IN GERMANY.
NOTE 11: PAX ENTERING INTO GERMANY AND WHO HAVE STAYED IN AN INTERNATIONAL RISK AREA BUT NOT IN A HIGH-INCIDENCE AREA OR AN AREA OF VIRUS VARIANT OF CONCERN WITHIN THE LAST 10 DAYS PRIOR TO ENTRY MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF A TEST FOR SARS-COV-2 NO LATER THAN 48 HOURS AFTER ENTRY TO THE COMPETENT AUTHORITY.

  MAY SELECT "AUTO". WHEN PLANNING AN "AUTO" COST INDEX, THE SYSTEM
  WILL REFERENCE THE SCHEDULED "TIME ENROUTE" OPTION AND ATTEMPT TO
  CHOOSE A COST INDEX WHICH CLOSELY MATCHES THIS VALUE. NOTE THAT
  THE "TIME ENROUTE" OPTION IS MEANT AS A GATE TO GATE TIME (AS
  INDICATED ON AN AIRLINE'S FLIGHT SCHEDULE, FOR EXAMPLE). IF A
  "TIME ENROUTE" OF 2:30 IS SELECTED, THE SYSTEM WILL SUBTRACT THE
  TAXI TIMES FROM THIS VALUE TO DETERMINE THE SCHEDULED AIR TIME. IT
  WILL THEN DETERMINE AND USE THE COST INDEX WHICH MATCHES THIS AIR
  TIME.
